@startuml
title TicketPlus - DDD Bounded Context Map
left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

actor Buyer
actor Organizer

component "API Gateway" as Gateway
component "Identity & Access\n[Identity]" as Identity
component "Catalog & Discovery\n[Upstream metadata owner]" as Catalog
component "Waiting Room\n[Admission control]" as Waiting
component "Reservation & Inventory\n[Availability owner]" as Reservation
component "Billing & Checkout\n[Saga coordinator]" as Checkout
component "Ticketing\n[Ticket lifecycle]" as Ticketing
component "Notification\n[Delivery]" as Notification
queue "Kafka\nVersioned domain events" as Kafka

Buyer --> Gateway
Organizer --> Gateway
Gateway --> Identity : token validation
Gateway --> Catalog : event queries
Gateway --> Waiting : admission
Gateway --> Reservation : seat map / lock
Gateway --> Checkout : checkout

Catalog --> Kafka : EventPublished
Waiting --> Reservation : admitted lock request
Reservation --> Kafka : InventoryChanged\nReservationExpired
Checkout --> Reservation : Confirm / Release
Checkout --> Kafka : PaymentSucceeded\nPaymentFailed
Kafka --> Catalog : inventory projection
Kafka --> Ticketing : issue ticket
Kafka --> Notification : send status message

note bottom of Catalog
  Never writes live availability.
  Search counts are projections.
end note

note bottom of Reservation
  Sole authority for AVAILABLE,
  LOCKED, and BOOKED transitions.
end note
@enduml

